-59907-000-1}}\n* {{cite book |ref={{harvid|Stackelberg|2009}}\n|last=Stackelberg |first=R. |title=Hitler's Germany: Origins, Interpretations, Legacies |year=2009 |publisher=Routledge |location=London |edition=2nd  |isbn=978-0-415-37331-9}}\n* {{cite book |ref={{harvid|Stapleton|2013}}\n|last=Stapelton |first=Timothy J. |title=A Military History of Africa: The Colonial Period: from the Scramble for Africa to the Algerian Independence War (ca. 1870\u20131963) |volume=II |publisher=ABC-CLIO |location=Santa Barbara, California |year=2013 |isbn=978-0-313-39570-3}}\n* {{cite encyclopedia |ref={{harvid|Stearns|Langer|2002}}\n|last1=Stearns |first1=Peter N. |last2=Langer |first2=William Leonard |title=The Encyclopedia of World History: Ancient, Medieval and Modern |year=2002 |publisher=Bartleby.com |location=New York |edition=6th, online |oclc=51671800}}\n* {{cite book |ref={{harvid|Sullivan|1999}} |editor-last=Martel |editor-first=G. |title=The Origins of the Second World War Reconsidered A. J. P. Taylor and the Historians |chapter=More than Meets the Eye: The Ethiopian War and the Origins of the Second World War |last=Sullivan |first=Barry |pages=[https://archive.org/details/originsofsecondw00gord_0/page/178 178\u2013203] |authorlink= |year=1999 |publisher=Routledge |location= |edition=2nd |isbn=978-0-415-16325-5 |chapter-url=https://archive.org/details/originsofsecondw00gord_0/page/178 }}\n{{refend}}\n\n===Journals===\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{cite journal |ref={{harvid|Cernuschi|1994}}\n|last=Cernuschi |first=Enrico |title=La resistenza sconosciuta in Africa Orientale |trans-title=The Unknown Resistance in East Africa |journal=Rivista Storica |language=Italian |date=December 1994 |oclc=30747124}}\n* {{cite journal |ref={{harvid|Clarke|1999}}\n|last=Calvitt Clark |first=J. |url=http://users.ju.edu/jclarke/wizzd.html |title=Japan and Italy squabble over Ethiopia: The Sugimura affair of July 1935 |journal=Selected Annual Proceedings of the Florida Conference of Historians |year=